stateDiagram-v2
    %% Data preparation view checked against load_config(), get_provider(),
    %% versioned cache guard, schema guard, bronze contract, coverage SLA, and adapter.prepare().
    direction TB

    [*] --> Config
    state "Configuration" as Config {
        direction TB
        [*] --> InstrumentYaml : instrument YAML
        InstrumentYaml --> FamilyDefaults : merge family defaults
        FamilyDefaults --> NormalizedConfig : normalize_config()
        NormalizedConfig --> [*]
    }

    Config --> FixedInputGuard : cache/version pin guard
    FixedInputGuard --> SourceRead : provider.fetch() or versioned cache read
    SourceRead --> VersionedCache : optional cache write
    VersionedCache --> BronzeContract : validate bronze contract
    SourceRead --> BronzeContract
    BronzeContract --> Quarantine : diverted bad rows
    BronzeContract --> CoverageSLA : coverage/freshness SLA
    CoverageSLA --> FamilySchemaGuard : required columns for family
    FamilySchemaGuard --> IngestionAudit : audit.snapshot("ingestion")
    IngestionAudit --> AdapterSelection : get_adapter(cfg)
    AdapterSelection --> PreparedData : adapter.prepare(clean_raw_df)
    PreparedData --> OptionPrep : options only: universe, IV, Greeks, PCP, expiry labels
    PreparedData --> AdapterAudit : audit.snapshot("adapter")
    OptionPrep --> AdapterAudit
    AdapterAudit --> [*]

    note right of PreparedData
        Adapter output is the shared prepared DataFrame
        and core_cfg consumed by downstream stages.
    end note

    note right of FixedInputGuard
        Local CSV inputs can pass the guard when
        file path and SHA-256 are pinned in config.
    end note

    note right of FamilySchemaGuard
        Family schema guard catches obvious YAML/data
        mismatches before adapter math runs.
    end note
